### View Component

The View component tracks and displays view counts:

```tsx
const View = async ({id}:{id:string}) => {
    const {views:totalviews} = await client.withConfig({useCdn:false}).fetch(STARTUP_VIEW_BY_ID,{id});

    after(async () => await writeClient
        .patch(id)
        .set({views: totalviews + 1})
        .commit())

    return (
        <div className="view-container">
            <div className="-top-2 absolute -right-2">
                <Ping/>
            </div>

            <p className="view-text">
                <span className="font-black">
                    {totalviews} Views
                </span>
            </p>
        </div>
    )
}
```

**Key Features:**
- Server component that fetches current view count
- Uses Next.js `after` function for post-render operations
- Updates the view count in Sanity CMS
- Visual ping animation to indicate real-time updates

